Question:
Find all numbers (as Strings) starting with '1'.
Input:
List<String> nums = Arrays.asList("10", "15", "8", "49", "98", "32", "15");

Solution:-
Java 8 Streams find strings starting with '1' using filter with startsWith("1"). For input, returns ["10", "15", "15"].

#Step-by-Step Logic
Stream the list via stream(). Filter with filter(num -> num.startsWith("1")). Collect to List<String> using Collectors.toList().

#Complete Implementation

import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.stream.Collectors;

public class NumbersStartingWith1 {
    public static List<String> findStartingWith1(List<String> nums) {
        return nums.stream()
                   .filter(num -> num.startsWith("1"))
                   .collect(Collectors.toList());
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        List<String> nums = Arrays.asList("10", "15", "8", "49", "98", "32", "15");
        List<String> result = findStartingWith1(nums);
        System.out.println(result);  // [10, 15, 15]
    }
}

Returns ["10", "15", "15"] preserving order/duplicates.

#Thought Process
startsWith("1") efficient prefix check. String method, case-sensitive. filter selects matches. toList() collects result. Simple predicate chain.

#Edge Cases Analysis
Empty list: [].
Null list: NPE on stream().
Null elements: null.startsWith("1") â†’ NPE; filter Objects::nonNull.
Empty strings: "" false.
Single "1": ["1"] true.
Leading zeros: "100" true.
